# SMTP (RFC 5321, tcp:25) control-channel command. Client sends `EHLO example.com\r\n` to the server. The
# whole message is kept verbatim (byte-perfect); the first line is parsed for display (command/argument).
# source: real capture — ubuntu:20.04 container, a python socket listening on 127.0.0.1:25 with a second
# python socket connecting and sending `EHLO example.com\r\n`, over the ethernet lo interface, captured
# with tcpdump (all-zero loopback MACs, ethertype 0800, IPv4/TCP dst port 25 with timestamp options).
